ers</span><hr size=1> Paladin Epics are probably one of the most difficult to achieve. For the lousy results it entails.<br>
<br>
It has been getting to the point where Paladins are loosing all the way around. Our epics are weak for the newer expansion we have gotten or Weapons that are available that are No drop to Magic or lore items. <br>
The Cleric hammer procs at least 20 times a mob. Plus their Yulp 5 to give mana regen. There average hits being 14 to 138 depending on level and buffs. <br>
Besides the fact that Melee clerics are causing more deaths because they are OOM or forget to heal because they are cought up in the battle.<br>
<br>
The Average Paladin at high levels and skill for a weapon miss 60% of the time. Our Epic does not proc but maybe 1 or 2 times a mob. Our average hit is about 14 to 175 More on an average of 80 to 130hp dam.<br>
<br>
Can anyone else see this?<br>
<br>
 I am starting to get frustrated because of the way they keep skipping over paladins. Our Soft cap for AC is 1250 from what I understand. So this means anything above 1250AC is pretty much useless.  Even with a Massive DragonClaw shard. Your average hit is around 45 to 125. With about 50% misses on each mob that cons Blue to a high level paladin. <br>
<br>
Is it Paladins in General or are we getting screwed?<br>
<br>
I would really like to hear others opinion on this matter...<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
